data.title: Good food, service not great
data.text:
First off, get the Mexican guacamole. Second, I've never had anything bad here. 
We had to send everything we ordered back, which was frustrating. Nothing showed up as it had been ordered, so we were frustrated. 
Decent little local place though.

data.title: great staff
data.text: the staff is super nice.  the food is pretty good too.... i love the salsa  and chips!  they have a pretty good patio area.

data.title: Typical Tex-Mex Menu
data.text: A chance stop for a late lunch. A number of cars in the lot always a good sign. An average Mexican restaurant.  Food had good flavor, dish proportions fairly typical.  Nothing to distinguish this restaurant yet nothing to keep me from recommending it either.  Pleasant lunch experience

data.title: Great Mexican and Margaritas !!
data.text: One of my favorite Mexican experiences..Great food and margaritas served by warm friendly staff.. I truly feel like a family member here.. Large scenic patio area which hosts great live music. Just a short walkable distance from downtown Roswell shops and sights.. 👍🏼👍🏼

data.title: Never Again
data.text:
We have been eating here for many years, before the name change.
The menu has changed recently and not for the better.
However, today will be the last time.
The wife and I ordered Steak Fajitas......and they were horrible.
The meat was tough and un-chewable.
The veggies were big chunks of onions and peppers with absolutely no seasoning and no flavor.
The waiter never asked how it was even though he picked up plates with plenty of steak still on them.
There are plenty of other places in the Roswell area that are better and we will not be back.

data.title: April 2015 they failed board of health inspection
data.text: Really disturbed by this as my family and I have visited here on multiple occasions.  Their score was a 62 or U for a variety of reasons that are outlined in the online report.  I will tell you that my family enjoyed the guacamole immensely.  Very sad they seem to have an issue here and hope they can correct it quickly

data.title: Authentic Mexican, Non-Chain
data.text: This place has a homey feel to it and you get the feel you that you are supporting a local business.  Their portions are very generous.  A solid thumbs up!

data.title: Good food
data.text: I came to El Zarape with my husband last night.  We sat outside and chips and salsa were delivered.  The salsa was delicious but the chips were a tad stale.  I ordered the tlalpeno soup and enchiladas acapulco and he got a burrito.  My soup was excellent, lots of chicken and veggies and cheese, I would definitely get the soup again.  The enchiladas were a little dry, not sure if they sat out waiting for something else to be ready or what.  The rice and beans were up to the standard I expect.  My husband said his burrito was "good" but he didn't have anything else to say (typical for him, he says that about everything!).  The service was pretty slow but the waitress was very pleasant and friendly.  Overall, I was pleased with our experience at El Zarape, and would go back if we didn't have even better Mexican food closer to home!

data.title: Good margaritas.  Terrible food.
data.text:
Between the boyfriend and me, we sampled burritos, tacos, enchiladas and the chili relleno.  Everything was terribly bland.  By far the worst Mexican restaurant I've been to in the Atlanta area and I have been to many. 

The margaritas were tasty and our server was very attentive.

data.title: Don't order the poblano chili !
data.text: I have been here off and on, mainly for the Speedy Gonzales which is ordinary but fine.  Yesterday we wanted to try some of their 'specialty' dishes so we ordered the Chili Poblano and the Guajillo Burrito and tortilla soup as an appetizer. The soup was fine, nicely spiced with big chunks of chicken.  The burrito was ok, though small portion for the price.  The Poblano was not edible.  If I hadn't done take-out I would have sent it back!  The chili was so tough neither fork nor knife could cut through it.  I finally ripped it apart and inside was a cold, hard blob of cheese. The rest of the meal was hot so I don't know what happened.  I don't know if they forgot to take the skin off or what.  I noticed they have a Trip Advisor sign in the window so I felt I needed to post this review. Very disappointing!

data.title: Good, cheap Mexican food
data.text: This is a great spot for chips/salsa and a margarita. All of the dishes on the menu seemed very common. I had the Fajitas Texanos, and it was good (the shrimp was not very good).

data.title: TERRIBLE SERVICE!!!!! DON'T ORDER ONLINE AT ALL!!!!!
data.text: I ordered online and was told I would receive my order within 45 minutes, an hour and a half later I called because I hadn't received my order, i was told that they don't know what happened, maybe they could get it to me soon! That was it! Really TERRIBLE service!!!!!!!!!!

data.title: One of our Fave Mexican restaurants
data.text: If you go on a Saturday night, like we did, they have music outside.  We had wonderful service, atmosphere, and food.  We choose to sit outside and recommend this (in season, of course).

data.title: My favorite neighborhood place to eat -- simple, inexpensive and good
data.text: If you are looking for fancy and elegant fine dining, don't stop here. But if you want a great meal and margarita and friendly service at an affordable price, this is the place. We've been going here for 12 years and I can't remember ever being  unhappy.  It is our last minute default, weekly trivia and party with friends place.

data.title: Our family favorite
data.text: Nothing fancy, but good, dependable food. Fast service. Great prices. Convenient. You get a lot of food the money at this Roswell standard.

data.title: Nothing fancy but the food and prices are worth the visit.
data.text: Good mexican food, but nothing exceptional.  Reasonable prices, attentive service and big portions.  If you want a nice environment you may be disappointed but if you are hungry this is the place.

data.title: Best Guacamole I've ever had
data.text: Yep, even when I was in Mexico the guacamole wasn't this good.  It's homemade with fresh tomatoes, lime juice... fantastic.  The place is a bit of a dive, maybe that's what makes it taste so good?  Typical Mexican fare; all good and the bill is a little more reasonable than the restaurants that are a few blocks down in the heart of Historic Roswell.  Just walk about 2 blocks south of the Historic District (on Atlanta St), right past the gas station and you'll find this hidden gem.

data.title: Best Guacamole, Really good food
data.text:
We just happened to be driving by El Zarape when we decided we had to stop to get some lunch.  It was already past 1:00pm when we pulled into their parking lot.

We weren't sure what to expect, because there was really nothing "special" about the appearance of the restaurant...not from the outside, and not from the inside. But we both agreed we wanted to eat Mexican food.  

This is the real deal, folks.  Not Tex-Mex, not Taco Bell, not Taco Mac, but what we considered (from our trips to Mexico over the past 30 years) to be authentic...without being a roadside stand, but a real restaurant where they have a complete bar, comfortable seating (although not much ambiance) and some really good food.

I suspect there might be other Fiesta type entertainment that goes on here during busier times of the day, or on weekends, because we saw stereo soundboards and other signs that suggested entertainment.  

All I know is the food was really good, and the guacamole was excellent and fresh!!  (Guacamole is my taste test in every Mexican restaurant, including those in Mexico.)

Prices for lunch ran between $5 to $8 per entree.  We checked the dinner entrees and they ran about $12 to $15 per entree.  We didn't have any alcoholic drinks so I can't comment on that.

I had the Enchilado Ranchero which was a large quantity for lunch, the pork was tender and juicy, and it was delicious.  My spouse had the Burrito Supremo and said it was really good.  It didn't look like any Burrito that you'd get at Taco Bell or other fast food restaurants, it was an entree that they can be proud to serve.

We checked out the bathrooms.  They could have used a little tending to...one was a little dirtier than I'd expect, and there were some missing or chipped tiles that should be replaced.  A little renovating would do a world of good, but then they'd probably have to charge a little more for their food.  

I noticed they had outdoor seating for the nicer weather (we were there in January and it was cold and raining out) but my guess is it's a popular place because it's on the main street in Roswell, near all the great little specialty shops, antiques, art galleries, etc.

Don't pass this place up.  We are definitely going back again.  They accepted credit cards and the checks were all computed and very modern in that sense.

data.title: Very good, basic, no frills Mexican food.
data.text:
My favorite here is the shrimp with chipolte sauce.  Carnitas also very good.
Margaritas excellent.
